@7    = ~There is no real lock, only a symbol of a hand.~
@8    = ~There is no way to open this door. The lock looks as if it was melted and then smashed.~
@9    = ~Dark clouds. Crooked trees. A cold mist that permeates your skin. This is what welcomes you into this land, predatory in its nature. As you set foot in it, it pulls you deeper and deeper into its realm. You are being ripped away from wherever you came from, with no mercy. I have heard this story many times before. And I have seen it with my own eyes.

The first few steps into this world echo with pain inside you. You walk an unknown path, unsteady, as wet clay splashes under your feet. You are trying to understand where you have landed, but the place offers no answers. Instead, it poses new questions and lays new layers of gloom, pressing you down into the ground.

What comes next are the cries. The howling. The cawing of ravens and crows that takes over your heart and mind. Finally, a new sound pierces through the cacophony: a distinct buzz.

I have seen others who woke up in this world. And I know what comes next. The feeling. One that can only be described as... dread.~ [L#RVINTR]
