@63   = ~Blood Honey
(Necromancy)

Level: 5
Range: 0
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None 

Casting the Blood Honey spell requires a small blood sacrifice. The caster deals 1d4 damage to themselves. This sacrifice allows one to summon one blood comb of dark, not-too-sweet, metallic-tasting honey. When eaten, it deals another 1d4 damage to the eater, however, it also reduces spellcasting time by 2 points for two rounds and by 1 point for three following rounds. It also provides a +3 bonus to caster level and a +3 bonus to Saving Throws vs. Necromancy for all five rounds.

The initial damage to the eater will be healed along with other damage, as after two rounds, the eater heals 3d4+4 damage. Vampires regain twice as much health that way.

If the honey isn't eaten in 16 hours, it is destroyed.~
