@69   = ~Necromancer's Journal~
@70   = ~This is a journal of the necromancer you encountered in one of the tombs of the Athkatla Graveyard. Only some of the entries remain legible.

Ches 20th 1364 DR
I understand now. The Dread. The Powers. The Prison. And everything they constitute combined. I feel the urge to find it, to reach the Prison, to feel it! I shall commence my preparations immediately. It may take years, but I won't give up.

Ches 2nd 1366 DR
It's been almost two years, but I'm still not giving up. And I have clearly made progress. I may know how to pass the mist, how to understand the Prison. Once I reach it, I will be able to harness its power. Unless... I decide to stay. To study it. To become like the mighty Dark Lord...

Marpenoth 13th 1367 DR
I know where to look for the last element, a book that describes the right symbols. It's in Amn. I should go there and... perhaps I should no longer delay the Opening. Perhaps that is where I should open the door to the Prison. There, however, may be others, not just Von Zarovich... It might be worth meeting them. Maybe they will teach me...~
@71   = ~Letter~
@72   = ~Dear Delique, 

It's my turn to stand guard, and I'm writing this letter, hoping the thought of you will keep me awake. The whole team is doing their best to watch each other's back, but... I feel so tired. And I miss you so much. Sleep is tempting me, and as I'm drifting away, I go straight into your arms, my love. 

I remember how we talked about starting something of our own. Our little shop. This will be my last adventure. No more wandering. I just need to survive the journey through the dark forest, endure a few more night watches, and... we'll see each other again.

Always yours,
Samvina~
@73   = ~Notes on Barovia~
@74   = ~It took me a while to understand what this place was... It's not easy to digest; it's a sort of prison after all. We're here because of Strahd von Zarovich; because of him, we need to exist in this place of dread and mists.

The mists that surround us are the prison bars, and I am not sure if they can be broken. Perhaps they may be bent for a moment, but I am certain they will regenerate. And it's quite clear only those with exceptional powers will be able to leave this accursed place behind, definitely not any common person! We are bound to live here surrounded by beasts that feast on our flesh and sanity.

Strahd rules these lands, and with such a creature as our "master", we need no enemies.

I have no means to confirm it, but I heard there are others like him. Other masters. And obviously, their servants.~
