@212  = ~Barovian Flora and Fauna~
@213  = ~Barovia is known for its beautiful forests. Many of them are rich in hardwood trees like cherry, hazelnut, beech, and oak, as well as other trees like alder, or fir.

These forests are the homeland of many wild animals: bears, wolves, deer, rabbits, rats, and hedgehogs. It would be rather unusual not to encounter blackbirds like ravens or jackdaws in the land of Barovia, but many do not know the land is also home to many owls, hawks, and other birds. People may also expect to find bats in the area. These are often associated with Barovia because of some dark legends regarding these animals.

Remember, adventurers, that our woods are also home to more hostile creatures: werewolves, giant spiders, and vipers. Take all necessary precautions to ensure the trip to our beautiful forests won't be your last.

STATISTICS: 

Weight: 1~
@214  = ~The History of Strahd von Zarovich~
@215  = ~Barovia is home to many men, women, animals, and creatures, but there aren't many like Strahd von Zarovich. He's also known as the Devil Strahd, The Dreadful One, and the Undead Count.

Numerous tales are being told about Strahd. Some say he is responsible for Barovia's current state of misery and danger. Those bitter would also say that only he could have inspired the taste for blood in oh so many other beings, all at once.

Only a few know that his parents, Barov von Zarovich and Ravenovia von Zarovich aren't his only relatives. Sergei von Zarovich and Sturm von Zarovich also left their mark on the realms, but it is Strahd that most people fear... or dream about.

STATISTICS: 

Weight: 1~
@216  = ~History of Roses~
@217  = ~This book describes many types of roses that grow in Barovia as well as other realms. It looks like it aspires to be a complete history of roses.

It doesn't only provide information on the plants themselves but also contains culinary recipes that include roses and suggestions on rose-scented perfume... Furthermore, it comprises tales and nursery rhymes about roses and creatures somehow linked to those flowers.

Since the book includes both real information and a work of fiction, it's hard to say which parts may be trusted and which only serve as fuel for imagination, fear, and desires.

STATISTICS: 

Weight: 1~
@218  = ~History of Oraşnou~
@219  = ~This book contains information about Oraşnou—a small hamlet located at the foot of the mountains in the land of Barovia.

If the book is to be trusted, there aren't many roads or paths that lead to Oraşnou. The village is isolated from the rest of Barovia, which makes some people consider it quite... gloomy.

There isn't much in this book that would help you on your journey.

STATISTICS: 

Weight: 1~
@220  = ~Letter from Strahd~
@221  = ~Dear Subject,

Your dedication to your research has earned my attention and even admiration, to some extent. While our plans regarding Barovia differ, I do believe those like the Bloodjackets make the heart of Barovia beat faster. And the faster the heart beats, the better the blood tastes.

I won't be visiting you anytime soon, but for all the amusements you provided, I gift you my old cloak. Let it be a token of my appreciation of our acquaintance.

I do not know if your husband will survive, but... it does not matter much, Evemorî Ernica-Bloodjacket. At least the two of you served as an inspiration to one another.

If he dies... make sure it wasn't for nothing. Let his passing be the beginning of something great. While I will not be there to observe what you make of it, I have a feeling you will come up with something grand.

With most vivid regards,
Strahd von Zarovich~
